reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Perfect size for my daughter’s bedroom. Easy enough to assemble and looks great!! Very happy with this one!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I love this table! I use it beside my bed & it holds everything that I need with plenty of extra space. The glass is pretty thick and doesn’t seem breakable - as you can see in the video, I knocked on it pretty hard & it’s very sturdy & makes a satisfying low-sounding thud. The magnetic closure is *very* secure - I could move the desk and the door wouldn’t pop down. I like that though, and don’t mind having to use two fingers to get it open because I’d rather it be sturdy. The paint job is really nice and they even painted the tips of the screws to make it blend nicely. It was very easy to put together, it took me about 30 minutes all in all. Even when it does move, the legs don’t wobble, as the entire structure is sound. I love this SO much and it’s a massive upgrade from what I had before. Plus, the outlets work gloriously and I love having a space to plug in my wires. There’s a little hole in the back to hide the wire for the outlet within the desk which is clever. Love it and definitely recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute end table but has weird cord placement.
reviews.reviewText: This end table looks super cute. We bought two of them, and they fit in with our living room decor perfectly.Assembly was very straightforward. The first one took me about 45 minutes to put together myself, and the second one took me about 30 minutes. I only really had one issue where on of the foot levelers had incorrect threading. I couldn't really get it to screw into any of the legs. I tried the other three that were in the package, and they all screwed in just fine, so I know it was the threading on this specific part. My husband had to pretty much force it in using other tools.As far as sturdiness goes, you get what you pay for. These seem okay, but I wouldn't want to put anything super fragile on them. That said, they are just as sturdy as I was expecting them to be for the price.My only real issue with these is the overall design with the power cord. It's designed to come out of the top corner of the back rather than the bottom corner. This would have been a super easy design fix by cutting a channel into the back of the shelf for the cord to come through. My husband is planning to do this ourselves because it seems like a major design flaw to have the cord come out from the top as you can see if from the front most of the time.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Adorable and practical
reviews.reviewText: I purchased these for my daughters room and they were perfect and reasonably priced. Some were $200 a piece. This was super easy to put together, my 9 year old wanted to help so I allowed her to. The trickiest part for me was the hinge but trial and error and I got that done. Directions were simple and straight forward. It's really sturdy. I got it in white. I love the tempered glass. Love that it has USB port and plug in charging station. My kids love them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best Night Stand
reviews.reviewText: I spent two weeks comparing and contrasting charging night stands on Amazon. If you’re anything like me don’t hesitate, this is the one!! Very sleek and modern design. Super fast and easy assembly. Charging works quickly. Only critique, I wish the top of the back boards were black. I prefer a seamless black look but that’s an easy fix.
